King Mansion, Jamaica. Restored primitive portrait of Joanna Smith, daughter of Christopher and Mary. Smith was the
builder of the house, prior to 1760.
The spinet is by Longman Clementi and Lo., London. It is one of two brought to this country in 1802. Loaned by the Lawrence family.

727039f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., north side, between 150th and 153rd Streets, showing in a set of four views the Rufus King house.  This place was partially erected in 1750 and extended from time to time.   In 1780 Widow Marsh conducted a tavern here.  Christopher Smith purchased it in 1781.   Amos Smith sold it in 1805 to Rufus King.  See other views for more data.

1922.
Views 1 and 4.
Views 2 and 3:  October 1924.

Eugene L. Armbruster.
